<item>
            <title>[TIKA-392] RTF parser smashes words together in subsequent table cells</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-392</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have an RTF document with the following snippet of content (it&apos;s an export of a private phone book so I can&apos;t share the full document):&lt;/p&gt;

{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\lang2055\langfe2055\langfenp2055\insrsid9461491\charrsid9461491 Fax / Phone Station\cell Fax / Phone #\cell }

&lt;p&gt;The extracted text is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fax / Phone StationFax / Phone&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note how the cell boundary between &quot;Station&quot; and &quot;Fax&quot; is lost.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
